					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13312688#post-4645484</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13312688/scp-4783#post-4645484</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2020 17:50:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Hydrails-EPSILON</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5348862</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I lived in Singapore before: I can easily envision the crowded HDB blocks and the daily Singlish of the daily lives.</p> <p>I also remember that it was some time till I was out of Singapore when I first found a more critical view of the country.</p> <p>I like this: the implication that Singapore and the Foundation have bad blood, that encounter with the Liang representatives, the suggestion that Singapore from its very beginning was a stronghold of&#8230; Well, not going to spoil it. (though I guess this is why you did not use the actual Prime Minister or even the Lees)</p> <p>And the final implication that despite the odds&#8230; The Foundation is going to fight (Containment Procedures basically have declared a war of annihilation)<br /> +1</p> <p>EDIT: Hmmm&#8230; That is Lee Hsien Loong. If so, why give him a different name if you are still using his face?</p> <p>Also, I think you should ask for permission from the writer of &quot;The Merion&quot; poem for permission to quote, be frank with what the SCP is.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
